article.story: ST. LOUIS -- — Great Osobor had 24 points in Utah State's 81-76 win against Saint Louis on Tuesday night. Osobor added 13 rebounds and three blocks for the Aggies (6-1). Isaac Johnson shot 7 for 9, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to add 16 points. Mason Falslev had 11 points and shot 5 for 8, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc. Gibson Jimerson led the way for the Billikens (5-3) with 28 points, five assists and two steals. Saint Louis also got 18 points and four assists from Michael Meadows. In addition, Terrence Hargrove Jr. had 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
